Package: gdiagram
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         graphviz
Description: Native multi-format diagram viewer supporting PlantUML and Mermaid
 gDiagram is a native GTK4/libadwaita application for viewing and editing
 diagrams in multiple formats including PlantUML and Mermaid. It provides
 real-time preview as you type, with full syntax highlighting and error detection.
 .
 Supported Formats:
  * PlantUML - 10+ diagram types (Sequence, Class, Activity, State, etc.)
  * Mermaid - 4 diagram types (Flowchart, Sequence, State, Class)
 .
 Features:
  * Native rendering using Graphviz (no Java or Node.js required)
  * Real-time diagram preview with debounced updates
  * Syntax highlighting for both PlantUML and Mermaid
  * Auto-format detection (.puml, .mmd file extensions)
  * Export to SVG, PNG, and PDF
  * Multi-tab editing
  * Dark mode support
  * Click-to-source navigation
